The mcescher package contains code ported or adapted from the following
third-party sources.  Each section gives the original author(s), the
corresponding source file, the governing license, and the primary
literature reference.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
airPLS  (R/airPLS.R)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Original MATLAB code: Zhimin Zhang, Central South University, 2011.
Ported to R by the mcescher authors.
License: BSD 3-Clause (see inst/licenses/LICENSE_BSD3.txt)

Primary reference:
  Zhang Z-M, Chen S, Liang Y-Z (2010).
  "Baseline correction using adaptive iteratively reweighted penalized
  least squares."
  Analyst, 135(5), 1138-1146.
  doi:10.1039/b922045c

Supporting references used in the original MATLAB code:
  Eilers PHC (2003). "A perfect smoother."
  Anal. Chem., 75(14), 3631-3636. doi:10.1021/ac034173t

  Eilers PHC, Boelens HFM (2005). "Baseline Correction with Asymmetric
  Least Squares Smoothing."

  Gan F, Ruan G, Mo J (2006). "Baseline correction by improved iterative
  polynomial fitting with automatic threshold."
  Chemom. Intell. Lab. Syst., 82(1-2), 59-65.
  doi:10.1016/j.chemolab.2005.08.009

Python port used as secondary reference:
  https://github.com/zmzhang/airPLS

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
airPLS variant by Shixuan Liu  (R/airPLS_liu.R)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Pure-R port of the Python implementation by Shixuan Liu (2014).
Source: https://github.com/zmzhang/airPLS
License: BSD 3-Clause (see inst/licenses/LICENSE_BSD3.txt)

Reference: Zhang et al. (2010), as above.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
arPLS / doArPLS  (R/doArPLS.R)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Original MATLAB code: Sung-June Baek, Spectroscopy Laboratory,
Chung-Ang University, 2015.
Ported to R by the mcescher authors.
License: BSD 3-Clause (see inst/licenses/LICENSE_BSD3.txt)

Reference:
  Baek S-J, Park A, Ahn Y-J, Choo J (2015).
  "Baseline correction using asymmetrically reweighted penalized least
  squares smoothing."
  Analyst, 140(1), 250-257.
  doi:10.1039/c4an01061b

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BEADS  (R/beads.R) and ABfilt helper  (R/sass.R)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Pure-R port of the MATLAB implementation by Xiaoran Ning
(Polytechnic School of Engineering, New York University).
Source: supplement to the reference below; also distributed via
  http://eeweb.poly.edu/iselesni/BEADS/
License: see inst/licenses/LICENSE_BEADS.txt

Reference:
  Ning X, Selesnick IW, Duval L (2014).
  "Chromatogram baseline estimation and denoising using sparsity (BEADS)."
  Chemometrics and Intelligent Laboratory Systems, 139, 156-167.
  doi:10.1016/j.chemolab.2014.09.014

Note: the ABfilt() helper in R/sass.R is the band-pass filter construction
routine shared between BEADS and SASS (Sparsity-Assisted Signal Smoothing)
and originates from the same NYU research group (Selesnick).

Reference for SASS:
  Selesnick IW (2017).
  "Sparsity-Assisted Signal Smoothing (revisited)."
  Wavelets and Sparsity XVII, Proc. SPIE 10394.
  doi:10.1117/12.2274187

